=== GLOBAL SECURITY HEADERS ===

/*

1. HSTS: Enforce HTTPS for future visits (High Security)

Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload

2. Prevent clickjacking (Security)

X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN

3. Prevent MIME type sniffing (Security)

X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff

4. Referrer Policy: Control what referrer information is sent (Privacy/Security)

Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin

5. Feature Policy: Control browser features (Performance/Security)

Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=()

=== CACHING HEADERS FOR STATIC ASSETS (Performance) ===

Images, CSS, and JavaScript files are cached aggressively to speed up repeat visits.

/style.css
Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
/script.js
Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
/.jpg
Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
/.png
Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
/*.ico
Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

=== CACHING FOR HTML PAGES (Less aggressive) ===

HTML pages need to be checked more often for fresh content.

/
Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
/balloons.html
Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
/personalisedGifts.html
Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
/matricCarePackages.html
Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
/blog.html
Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate